lemon zest and garlic into mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add bread and reserved chopped herbs and chop <b>10-15 sec\/speed 7<b>, or until a roughly chopped consistency is achieved. Transfer onto prepared baking tray and set aside."},{"content":"Place hazelnuts into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer onto prepared baking tray with breadcrumb-herb mixture, then drizzle with olive oil and lemon juice. Bake for 13-15 minutes (180°C) until crunchy."},{"content":"Allow to cool then transfer into a sealable container for up to 3 days."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Root vegetables"},{"content":"Place water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position, then weigh beetroot into it. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set Varoma aside."},{"content":"Place a large serving bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh Dutch carrots, purple carrots, parsnip, turnip or swede and avocado oil into it. Combine well with spatula."},{"content":"Place Varoma dish back into position and transfer half of the vegetables on top of beetroot. Insert Varoma tray and transfer remaining vegetables onto it. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>15-20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, or until vegetables are cooked."},{"content":"Transfer vegetables onto a serving platter, season with salt and pepper, then garnish with reserved pangrattato. Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Use pangrattato sprinkled over turkey and other roasted meats.","Pangrattato can be premade and frozen for up to 3 months. Simply defrost in a hot oven for a few minutes before using.","For flavour purposes, sourdough is best used in this recipe; however any type of bread can be used.","Substitute the avocado oil and salt in this recipe with any of the flavoured oils or salts from the homemade gift section."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","40m","8 portions"]}